The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 October is 5,413 (626.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 October, there were 659 new confirmed cases (76.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 October, there were 407 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 62% ( 252 extra cases).
